 "name": "beef stock", "slug": "beef-stock"}, {"id": 29647, "name": "butter", "slug": "butter"}, {"id": 29846, "name": "carrot", "slug": "carrot"}, {"id": 29886, "name": "celery", "slug": "celery"}, {"id": 30080, "name": "muscovado sugar", "slug": "muscovado-sugar"}, {"id": 29723, "name": "olive oil", "slug": "olive-oil"}, {"id": 29730, "name": "onion", "slug": "onion"}, {"id": 29651, "name": "plain flour", "slug": "plain-flour"}, {"id": 30775, "name": "thyme", "slug": "thyme"}, {"id": 44447, "name": "topside of beef", "slug": "topside-of-beef"}, {"id": 29744, "name": "white wine", "slug": "white-wine"}], "meal-type": [{"id": 30100, "name": "Dinner", "slug": "dinner"}, {"id": 29700, "name": "Main course", "slug": "main-course"}], "nutrition": [{"id": 29655, "name": "Low calorie", "slug": "low-calorie"}, {"id": 29644, "name": "Low salt", "slug": "low-salt"}], "occasion": [{"id": 29880, "name": "Sunday lunch", "slug": "sunday-lunch"}], "planning": [{"id": 29643, "name": "Freezable", "slug": "freezable"}], "publication": [{"id": 57786, "name": "February 2013", "slug": "february-2013-good-food-magazine"}], "post_tag": [{"id": 53256, "name": "\u00a0Josh Eagleton", "slug": "josh-eagleton"}, {"id": 29672, "name": "2 of 5-a-day", "slug": "2-of-5-a-day"}, {"id": 30978, "name": "Cheaper cuts", "slug": "cheaper-cuts"}, {"id": 29940, "name": "Comfort Food", "slug": "comfort-food"}, {"id": 44446, "name": "Comfort food without the calories", "slug": "comfort-food-without-the-calories"}, {"id": 36648, "name": "Diet", "slug": "diet"}, {"id": 29760, "name": "Folate", "slug": "folate"}, {"id": 29664, "name": "Iron", "slug": "iron"}, {"id": 30737, "name": "Jane Hornby", "slug": "jane-hornby"}, {"id": 30772, "name": "Low calorie", "slug": "low-calorie"}, {"id": 29989, "name": "Make ahead", "slug": "make-ahead"}, {"id": 40823, "name": "Slow-roast", "slug": "slow-roast"}, {"id": 30268, "name": "Sunday roast", "slug": "sunday-roast"}, {"id": 31910, "name": "Winter", "slug": "winter"}], "rating": [{"name": "1 Star+", "slug": "1-star"}, {"name": "2 Star+", "slug": "2-star"}, {"name": "3 Star+", "slug": "3-star"}, {"name": "4 Star+", "slug": "4-star"}], "calories": [{"name": "Up to 500 kcal", "slug": "up-to-500-kcal"}, {"name": "Up to 750 kcal", "slug": "up-to-750-kcal"}, {"name": "Up to 1000 kcal", "slug": "up-to-1000-kcal"}, {"name": "Up to 1500 kcal", "slug": "up-to-1500-kcal"}], "servings": [{"name": "4 servings", "slug": "4-servings"}], "total-time": [{"name": "Over 1 hour", "slug": "over-1-hour"}]}, "act_time": 150, "act_yields": "4 serving(s)", "act_ingredients": ["1kg silverside or topside of beef with no added fat", "2 tbsp olive oil", "8 young carrots, tops trimmed (but leave a little, if you like)", "1 celery stick, finely chopped", "200ml white wine", "600ml rich beef stock", "2 bay leaves", "500g onion", "a few thyme sprigs", "1 tsp butter", "1 tsp light brown or light muscovado sugar", "2 tsp plain flour"], "act_instructions": "Heat oven to 160C/140C fan/gas 3. Rub the meat with 1 tsp of the oil and plenty of seasoning. Heat a large flameproof casserole dish and brown the meat all over for about 10 mins. Meanwhile, add 2 tsp oil to a frying pan and fry the carrots and celery for 10 mins until turning golden.\nLift the beef onto a plate, splash the wine into the hot casserole and boil for 2 mins. Pour in the stock, return the beef, then tuck in the carrots, celery and bay leaves, trying not to submerge the carrots too much. Cover and cook in the oven for 2 hrs. (I like to turn the beef halfway through cooking.)\nMeanwhile, thinly slice the onions. Heat 1 tbsp oil in a pan and stir in the onions, thyme and some seasoning. Cover and cook gently for 20 mins until the onions are softened but not coloured. Remove the lid, turn up the heat, add the butter and sugar, then let the onions caramelise to a dark golden brown, stirring often. Remove the thyme sprigs, then set aside.\nWhen the beef is ready, it will be tender and easy to pull apart at the edges. Remove it from the casserole and snip off the strings. Reheat the onion pan, stir in the flour and cook for 1 min. Whisk the floury onions into the beefy juices in the casserole, to make a thick onion gravy. Taste for seasoning. Add the beef and carrots back to the casserole, or slice the beef and bring to the table on a platter, with the carrots to the side and the gravy spooned over.", "act_image": "https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2020/08/recipe-image-legacy-id-1222463_11-7eaf5a2.jpg", "act_nutrients": {"calories": "487 calories", "fatContent": "17 grams fat", "saturatedFatContent": "5 grams saturated fat", "carbohydrateContent": "19 grams carbohydrates", "sugarContent": "15 grams sugar", "fiberContent": "5 grams fiber", "proteinContent": "6 grams protein", "sodiumContent": "1 milligram of sodium"}}